parent":"257","text":"Criterio 1 -> sintomas agudos (min-horas) de piel/mucosas + compromiso resp/hipotension","guid":"J9vBwYrJQw2qV-UkMeGldg","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"257","text":"Criterio 2 -> dos o mas: piel, resp, CV, GI, tras exposicion a probable alergeno","guid":"RVJPP0J2RLSnUr6ghMs5Yw","children":[]},{"id":"260","parent":"257","text":"Criterio 3 -> hipotension tras exposicion a alergeno CONOCIDO del paciente","guid":"tiUJNLYfRTK2tK1K5mheiQ","children":[]},{"id":"261","parent":"257","text":"Sensibilidad criterios NIAID -> 96.7 porciento -> PMID:22051696","guid":"LZ0HCDAJSR-WtuIMAZ9YAQ","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"257","text":"Especificidad criterios NIAID -> 82.4 porciento -> PMID:22051696","guid":"ETbwpj9ZRI6Et0Ow-uYeGw","children":[]}]},{"id":"263","parent":"256","text":"HALLAZGOS CLINICOS (cabecera)","guid":"ixk52BYZT0afaHIHrOmMvA","children":[{"id":"264","parent":"263","text":"Sintomas cutaneos + compromiso respiratorio agudo -> [definitorio dentro NIAID criterio 1]","guid":"YFbtFnrmTQuIPCfXl-USAQ","children":[]},{"id":"265","parent":"263","text":"Hipotension post-exposicion alergeno conocido -> [definitorio NIAID criterio 3]","guid":"3PQ7hCpIQw2bExpjuD6bDA","children":[]},{"id":"266","parent":"263","text":"Angioedema agudo + estridor -> compromiso via aerea","guid":"-nu0RkcDSlapq8LNLXchOw","children":[]},{"id":"267","parent":"263","text":"Broncoespasmo nuevo post-exposicion -> criterio respiratorio NIAID","guid":"FfMj99pGSXyYRv4gyZxp-w","children":[]}]},{"id":"268","parent":"256","text":"HALLAZGOS LABORATORIO","guid":"wgybsQ3nQYqHaSPzpgU6Zg","children":[{"id":"269","parent":"268","text":"Triptasa serica >11.4 ng/mL (0-3h post-evento) -> alto LR+ especifico, Sens 30-50 -> PMID:24084075","guid":"4WUt-_quRC-apiEODSJxSQ","children":[]},{"id":"270","parent":"268","text":"Criterio WAO 2020 -> Triptasa post > (basal x 1.2) + 2 ng/mL -> PMID:22041891","guid":"X1HJej4MTTSJ2T3D4QgVdw","children":[]},{"id":"271","parent":"268","text":"Triptasa NORMAL no descarta anafilaxia","guid":"iX48hWRZQ0GGuwfFg-3bQQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"272","parent":"256","text":"INTERPRETACION","guid":"ZY6-6-TySqWcKS2TlPWqgA","children":[{"id":"273","parent":"272","text":"Diagnostico es CLINICO por criterios compuestos NIAID/FAAN","guid":"IQ11ibJgSAy3YQ7uVOpf9g","children":[]},{"id":"274","parent":"272","text":"Triptasa confirma pero NO descarta","guid":"SX_LHbpDQ9mgctvZnzWKKg","children":[]},{"id":"275","parent":"272","text":"LRs de hallazgos individuales no consolidados formalmente (diagnostico por criterio)","guid":"NQzSkajRRtGTbllBXQCC7g","children":[]}]},{"id":"276","parent":"256","text":"GERIATRIA","guid":"WY6BFzQ7Q5C-Ilzouidf8A","children":[{"id":"277","parent":"276","text":"En AM la hipotension puede ser la unica manifestacion (sin urticaria)","guid":"kmd2KBO0ROOjDh7tCQH4ag","children":[]},{"id":"278","parent":"276","text":"IECA/betabloqueadores pueden enmascarar o potenciar","guid":"euzc9l4sQiKmTgQHGpBVMQ","children":[]},{"id":"279","parent":"276","text":"Adrenalina IM 0.3-0.5 mg sigue siendo primera linea, SIN contraindicacion absoluta por edad","guid":"oP_OVBLMT_uphCydrCDFvg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"280","parent":"0","text":"REFERENCIAS","guid":"S3ETJAySSsOlokwtvPOYCw","children":[{"id":"281","parent":"280","text":"Ventura 2022 → anafilaxia en adulto mayor (PMID:36165408, DOI:10.1097/ACI.0000000000000855)","guid":"3svC1tWKRAyXMWHZrG2LDw","children":[]},{"id":"282","parent":"280","text":"Pourmand 2018 → revision bifasica (PMID:29759531, DOI:10.1016/j.ajem.2018.05.009)","guid":"WV3UmcU1RtOdh2CuzFNlqg","children":[]},{"id":"283","parent":"280","text":"Rohacek 2014 → incidencia/mortalidad bifasica (PMID:24725226, DOI:10.1111/all.12404)","guid":"yaBiOk1CQsqcqXZydvhwaA","children":[]},{"id":"284","parent":"280","text":"Santos 2024 → guias EAACI alergia alimentaria (PMID:39473345, DOI:10.1111/all.16345)","guid":"EEqt3NNPR0uJ5EVbn8BkOw","children":[]},{"id":"285","parent":"280","text":"Lee 2024 → anafilaxia por remimazolam